Question.Text: A 31-Year-Old Man from Guatemala With several minutes of weakness and numbness of the leg. Two weeks previously, he also had two episodes of facial twitching that subsided without intervention after 10 seconds. Imaging reveals parenchymal calcified lesions, complex cystic structures in the subarachnoid space and an old lacunar infarct proximal to a cyst with a normal CT angiography
